The Telegraph - Calcutta
		 Wednesday, September 25, 2002 				 Ganga to replace Lara
																								St. Johns (Antigua): The West Indies selectors have called-up Darren Ganga to replace Brian Lara for the tour of India next month.																								Ganga, 23, a right-handed opening batsman, has played 12 Tests scoring 563 runs at an average of 20.85. 																								He was captain of the West Indies A-team that recently toured England and Canada.																								West Indies play three Tests and seven one-day Internationals in India.																								Lara was hospitalised with suspected hepatitis after scoring 111 against Kenya in a Champions Trophy match in Colombo last week.  (AFP)
